KAMAGUGU &#8211; Fifteen people are in a critical condition when a taxi and a bakkie collided on the KaMagugu Road this morning.Mpumalanga Emergency medical services&#8217; Mr AJ Dreyer said their paramedics treated 22 patients at the scene which were transported to Rob Ferreira Hospital.Two patients were slightly injured, five with moderate injuries and 15 were in a critical condition.The accident occurred in the exact same area as the accident which happened yesterday when a taxi&#8217;s came off and the driver control and overturned with school children inside it. Thirteen injured learners were transported to Rob Ferreira Hospital.